The Hawks shut down 19 illegal sites and confiscated gambling machines computers and money at several buildings. CAPE TOWN The Hawks believe more people are involved in illegal online gambling syndicates in the North West and Northern Cape where three people were arrested.The elite investigative unit shut down 19 illegal sites and confiscated gambling machines, computers and money at several buildings during raids yesterday.The 21 buildings, believed to be used for the activities, have been under surveillance for months.Hawks spokesperson in the Northern Cape Philani Nkwalase said, In the Northern Cape in 11 towns we seized equipment and money so a lot of people will be arrested as investigations continue. The arrested trio will face corruption, money laundering and racketeering charges, among others, when they appear in the Kimberly Magistrates Court on Monday.